It is illegal to have an abortion. Abortion after 12 weeks of pregnancy is most common for medical reasons and occurs in two to four percent of pregnancies. Thirteen percent of abortions happen after 28 weeks. Maternal death from unsafe abortions is estimated at four percent of maternal deaths in Cameroun.

Couples who are having trouble conceiving may face pressure and discrimination. People may whisper, teasing or judging about a couple’s inability to have children, even though the people may be planning to adopt or wish to be childless.

Mistrust of fertility specialists exists because of “failed” feeble IVF or infertility treatments.
